This section will define the customer requirements that are required for the camera to function and its various features. Each requirement specified in this section is associated with a specific customer need that will be satisfied. The requirements are the directly observable features and functions of the camera that will be encountered by its users. Requirements specified in this section are created with, and must not be changed without, specific agreement of the intended customer/user/sponsor.

\subsection{Minimum of 10 FPS}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will provide a user with a minimum stream of 10 FPS/
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
The camera needs to be able to maintain 10 FPS under load/
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Critical

\subsection{10x Zoom}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will have up to 10x zoom and be controllable from the user interface.
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
None
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Critical

\subsection{Day/Night Functionality}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will need to have the ability to function in both day and night.
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
None
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Critical

\subsection{Pan and Tilt Control}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will have the ability for users to control the current pan and tilt settings of the camera.
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
None
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Critical

\subsection{Weather Resistance}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will have the ability to resist certain weather conditions such as snow and rain.
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
The camera will only be rated for a certain temperature range and if exceeded could damage the camera.
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Critical

\subsection{Maximum of 5W Power Consumption}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will have the ability to resist certain weather conditions such as snow and rain.
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
The camera will only be rated for a certain temperature range and if exceeded could damage the camera.
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Critical

\subsection{Heater}
\subsubsection{Description}
The camera will have a controllable heater to help melt snow or other obstructions off the camera dome.
\subsubsection{Source}
Traffic Net
\subsubsection{Constraints}
None
\subsubsection{Standards}
None
\subsubsection{Priority}
Low
